Senate President Ahmed Lawan has stated that President Buhari is in a hurry to develop the country. Lawan said this while speaking at a function in Kwara State over the weekend.  The Senate president, who urged Nigerians to continue to support the Buhari-led government, said the National Assembly would continue to partner with the executive arm to develop the country. “The federal government of President Muhammadu Buhari is in a hurry to develop Nigeria. In four years between 2019 and 2023 by the grace of God, Nigeria would have been turned into an infrastructure laboratory because every part of Nigeria from East to the West to the North to the South would have been impacted.’”he said  SOURCE .....drum up support for Kwara State Governor and Senators for re-electionBy Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan has said that the government of President Muhammadu Buhari is in a hurry to develop Nigeria. Lawan made the remarks on Saturday while on a visit… In "Politics" By Naomi Sharang Abuja -  The Leader of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, on Monday lauded the President Muhammadu Buhari-led administration for restoring relative normalcy to the Northeast. Lawan made the commendation when the Northeast Youths Coalition for President Buhari paid him a courtesy visit in Abuja. According to him, when… In "News" By Ismaila Chafe Abuja - President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan says henceforth the National Assembly (NASS) will ensure the passage of the nation’s appropriation bill within three months of its submission by the Executive arm of government. Lawan stated this known when he fielded questions from State House correspondents… In "Politics"